# `break` outside any enclosing loop.
#
# Ideally the HLL type-checker (`hll::type_check`) rejects this with
# a HTC-* error before lowering runs; today it doesn't, so the
# HLO-BreakOutsideLoop guard in lowering fires as an internal
# compiler error. This fixture pins current behavior — when
# type_check grows the check, update the .err.expected to the new
# HTC-* diagnostic.
fn f() {
  break;
}
